content:
Guidelines and Limits for Einstein Conversation Mining Data

Einstein Conversation Mining identifies trends with your conversation data, enabling you to build new capabilities for your bot, update processes, and write knowledge articles.

Einstein Conversation Mining reports support English only. For Email-to-Case reports, only the first email in a thread is used. Web-to-Case reports are not supported. Enhanced Conversations reports are not supported in sandbox environments.

You can view data used to build contact reasons by clicking summary names or "View Details" in Top Recommendations. Click "Download" in Topics for a CSV file of all contact reasons associated with a topic. Click "Download" on the contact reason detail page for a CSV file of up to 500 excerpts.

For Email-to-Case and Chat conversations, click "View Transcript" to view the transcript snippet. For Enhanced Conversations and Web-to-Case conversations, this button takes you to the transcript record or Case record.

Transcript Record Count represents transcripts used to generate reports and does not relate to Conversation Reason Excerpts generated. There are limits on Conversation Reason Excerpts: 500 utterances per conversation reason, 3,000 excerpts per conversation reason when ingested into Data Cloud using Ingestion API, and 100 max conversation reasons per bot session and agent session stored.

Only 100 max conversation reasons per bot session and agent session are stored.
title: Guidelines for Einstein Conversation Mining Data
